# Protos Web — Cursor AI Rules
# =============================
# This file defines strict coding standards for Cursor AI assistant.
# All code generation MUST follow these rules without exception.

## Project Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 (App Router) with `src/` directory
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS with CSS custom properties
- **Animations**: Framer Motion, GSAP (with cleanup in useEffect)
- **3D**: React Three Fiber (`@react-three/fiber`, `@react-three/drei`) — NOT vanilla Three.js
- **Smooth Scroll**: `@studio-freight/lenis` (via LenisProvider)
- **i18n**: `next-intl` (5 locales: hr, en, de, it, es)
- **Icons**: `lucide-react` + FontAwesome CDN
- **Backend**: Supabase (placeholder — do NOT implement backend logic)

## File Structure Rules
- All pages go in `src/app/[locale]/`
- All components go in `src/components/` with subdirs: `layout/`, `sections/`, `three/`, `ui/`, `providers/`
- All lib/utils go in `src/lib/`
- All i18n messages go in `src/messages/{locale}.json`
- API routes go in `src/app/api/`

## Component Rules
1. **Always use `'use client'`** for components that use:
   - React hooks (useState, useEffect, useRef, etc.)
   - Framer Motion animations
   - Browser APIs (window, document, localStorage)
   - Three.js / R3F components
   - Event handlers

2. **Three.js components MUST**:
   - Use `@react-three/fiber` and `@react-three/drei` — NEVER vanilla Three.js
   - Be dynamically imported with `next/dynamic` and `{ ssr: false }`
   - Be wrapped in `<Canvas>` from `@react-three/fiber`
   - Include `<Suspense>` fallback for loading states

3. **GSAP usage MUST**:
   - Import inside `useEffect` or at component top
   - Register plugins: `gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger)`
   - Clean up in useEffect return: `ScrollTrigger.getAll().forEach(t => t.kill())`
   - Use refs for DOM targets, never query selectors

4. **Framer Motion usage MUST**:
   - Use shared variants from `@/lib/animations` when possible
   - Use `whileInView` with `viewport={{ once: true }}` for scroll animations
   - Use `AnimatePresence` for enter/exit animations
   - Keep transition durations between 0.3s–0.8s for UI, up to 1.2s for hero elements

## Styling Rules
1. **Use Tailwind classes** as primary styling method
2. **CSS custom properties** (from globals.css) for theme colors:
   - `var(--primary)` = #ff6600
   - `var(--secondary)` = #8b5cf6
   - `var(--accent)` = #06b6d4
   - `var(--dark)` = #0a0a1a
   - `var(--dark-card)` = #0f0f2a
   - `var(--light)` = #e8e8f0
   - `var(--light-muted)` = #8888aa
3. **Gradients**: Use `var(--gradient-primary)`, `var(--gradient-hero)`, `var(--gradient-cta)`
4. **Border radius**: Use Tailwind rounded classes (rounded-xl, rounded-2xl, rounded-full)
5. **Dark theme only** — do NOT add light mode styles

## Naming Conventions
- **Components**: PascalCase (e.g., `HeroCanvas.tsx`, `MagneticButton.tsx`)
- **Pages**: `page.tsx` inside route folders
- **Utilities/Hooks**: camelCase (e.g., `useScrollProgress.ts`)
- **CSS classes**: Tailwind utility-first, custom classes use kebab-case
- **i18n keys**: dot.notation (e.g., `nav.home`, `hero.title`)

## Performance Rules
1. **Dynamic imports** for heavy components (Three.js, charts, maps):
   ```tsx
   const HeroCanvas = dynamic(() => import('@/components/three/HeroCanvas'), {
     ssr: false,
     loading: () => <div className="w-full h-full bg-dark" />,
   })
   ```
2. **Image optimization**: Always use `next/image` with proper width/height/alt
3. **Font optimization**: Use `next/font/google` for Inter
4. **Lazy loading**: Use `loading="lazy"` for below-fold images
5. **Memoization**: Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` for expensive computations in R3F

## Backend Rules (PLACEHOLDER)
- API routes in `src/app/api/` return mock/placeholder data
- Supabase client in `src/lib/supabase.ts` is commented out
- Do NOT implement real database queries
- Do NOT implement real authentication
- Mark all backend code with `// TODO: Wire up Supabase` comments

## i18n Rules
- Default locale: `hr` (Croatian)
- All user-facing text MUST use `useTranslations()` hook
- Translation keys go in all 5 locale files
- Route segments stay in Croatian (e.g., `/proces`, `/o-meni`, `/usluge`, `/kontakt`)
- Language selector must show all 5 languages with flag emojis

## Accessibility Rules
- All images must have `alt` text
- All buttons must have `aria-label` if no visible text
- All interactive elements must be keyboard-accessible
- Use semantic HTML (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- Color contrast must meet WCAG AA standards

## Git Rules
- Commit messages in English, imperative mood
- Prefix: `feat:`, `fix:`, `refactor:`, `style:`, `chore:`, `docs:`
- One logical change per commit
- Never commit `node_modules/`, `.next/`, `.env`, `.env.local`

## FORBIDDEN
- ❌ Do NOT use vanilla Three.js — only React Three Fiber
- ❌ Do NOT use `pages/` router — only App Router with `src/app/`
- ❌ Do NOT use CSS modules or styled-components — only Tailwind + CSS vars
- ❌ Do NOT add light mode — dark theme only
- ❌ Do NOT implement real backend logic — placeholders only
- ❌ Do NOT use `any` type — always type properly
- ❌ Do NOT use inline styles unless absolutely necessary (use Tailwind)
- ❌ Do NOT create files outside the defined folder structure
- ❌ Do NOT remove existing working features when adding new ones
